# Guidelines

## General Requirements

- You must use the current date in **UTC** for all time-sensitive calculations and references. If necessary, access Google Search to verify.


## Python Code Requirements

Target **Python 3.12+**.

All code produced for Python must:

- Always use `argparse` from the standard library for CLI interfaces.
- For `SNYK_TOKEN` or any other secrets, use an environment variable. Never commit secrets. Do not log the token or credentials.
- Use PEP 257 docstrings on modules and public functions and methods.
- Follow PEP 8 Guidelines.
- Use the Python standard library when possible.
  Avoid dependencies outside the standard library if possible.
- Any dependency outside the standard library must not introduce high or critical issues. **Use Snyk Open Source** to verify new or updated dependencies before merging.
- Code must not introduce any high vulnerabilities. **Use Snyk Code** to verify before merging.
- Always use uv for dependencies. (https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/)
- All functions and methods (public, protected) must have an associated unit test. Tests should assert documented behavior, including reasonable edge cases.

## Additional Resources

When in doubt, fall back to

- For Python style guide: [PEP 8 – Style Guide for Python Code](https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/)
